section.section:
If a seller or financial institution establishes an account for the use of a buyer, the seller or financial institution shall confirm the fact to the buyer in writing. The confirmation shall be in type no smaller than elite typewriter characters and shall contain:
A clear and understandable statement of the amount or the rate of the finance charge;
A legend that the buyer may pay at any time the entire balance without incurring any additional charge for prepayment;
A statement which advises the buyer of his right under § 12-510 of this subtitle to an answer to a written inquiry concerning the status of his account; and
Unless set out in a copy of the application form delivered to the buyer, the legend required by subsection (e)(2) of this section.

text.section:
Before the first payment on an account is due, other than any down payment, and within 40 days after each purchase, the holder of a retail credit account shall inform the buyer in writing of:
The cash sale price of the goods or services purchased;
The amount of any down payment;
A general description of the type of goods or services and the date of each purchase;
If the account is a closed end account:
The amount of the finance charge;
The time sale price;
The amount of each installment due, expressed in dollars; and
The time or period of the payment of each installment; and
If the account is an open end account:
The amount or the rate of the finance charge on the outstanding balance; and
The method of determining the outstanding balance pursuant to § 12-506(c) of this subtitle.
